  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. The applicable regulatory requirement is FDA Guidance for Industry and FDA Staff — Reporting of Computational Modeling Studies in Medical Device Submissions (2016), which mandates demonstration of model credibility commensurate with model risk. A Requirement node capturing this obligation is embedded in the package narrative; however, the top-level bindsRequirement link to that node is absent from this record. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels at MRL 5), 6 factors not assessed. Decision: Accepted for Minimal-profile demonstration purposes.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
