      "name": "Bench-scale hemolysis index comparison — FDA generic pump five operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis compared against experimental measurements at five flow-speed combinations. Mean absolute error 18.4%; predicted values exceed measured values at high-shear operating points, indicating model over-prediction bias under VAD conditions."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/cou2-monte-carlo-uq",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification — hemolysis prediction intervals",
      "description": "Monte Carlo sampling across rheological and power-law exponent uncertainty ranges (n=2000 runs). 95% prediction interval spans factor of 2.3 around point estimate; interval does not exclude clinical threshold at worst-case operating point."
    }
  ],
  "hasRequirement": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/fda-cm-guidance-2016-mrl5",
    "type": "Requirement",
    "name": "FDA Computational Modeling Guidance — MRL 5 credibility obligation",
    "description": "Per FDA Guidance for Industry and FDA Staff: Reporting of Computational Modeling Studies in Medical Device Submissions (2016), submissions relying on computational models at the highest model risk level must provide documented evidence of model credibility across all applicable ASME V&V 40 credibility factors. All credibility factor achieved levels must meet or exceed required levels before the model may serve as primary evidence for device acceptance."
  },
